===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|almande|lang=fro}}, from [[Romanic]] *{{term||amendla}} (with ''-l-'' in French and Spanish, probably by confusion with similar Arabic words), from {{etyl|la}} {{term|amygdala|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἀμυγδάλη|sc=polytonic|lang=grc|tr=amugdala}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈɑːmənd/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑmənd/}}, {{IPA|/ˈɑlmənd/}}, {{IPA|/æmənd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-almond.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{countable}} A type of [[tree]] [[nut]].
# {{countable}} A small [[deciduous]] tree, {{taxlink|Prunus dulcis|species}}, that produces almonds.
#* '''2004''', {{w|Richard Fortey}}, ''The Earth'', Folio Society 2011, p. 3:
#*: In early March the '''almonds''' are in flower, delicately pink, and there are washes of bright daffodils beneath the orchard trees; you can see women gathering them for market.
# {{uncountable}} The [[colour]] of the [[kernel]] of an almond without its [[shell]] and thin [[seed coat]], a [[creamy]] off-[[white]] colour.
#: {{color panel|almond|FFEBCD}}<!--this is the hex tripled used for the X11 BlanchedAlmond color-->
# {{uncountable}} The color of an almond still covered by its skin, a shade of brown.
#: {{color panel|almond|A67B5B}}

